.SH "SYNOPSIS"
Here you will find a list of all the available topics for help related to \fBDalma\fR and how to call for help
.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Users can request help on any specific topic using the following command:
.
.P
\fBman dalma\-<topic>\fR
.
.SH "MAIN TOPICS"
.
.SS "where \'topic\' can be one of:"
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBstorage\fR : Display information about the different filesystems and how to use them
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBqueues\fR : Display the different login information and when to use them
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBmodules\fR : NYUME login description\. How to access to the available software in the system
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBsoftware\fR : List of the available login
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBsystem\fR : System description
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBlogin\fR : How to log into the system, from inside and outside NYUAD
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBcompiling\fR : Compilation best practices and guidelines
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBget_account\fR : Requesting/renewing an account in Dalma
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBdata_movement\fR : How to move data efficiently in/out Dalma
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBslurm_environment\fR : Environment variables set by SLURM during the job lifetime
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBslurm_commands\fR : Commands most commonly used by users
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBslurm_sbatch\fR : sbatch options to be used inside the submission script or invoking \'sbatch\' from the command line
.
.IP "" 0
.
